    end
  end
end
```

7. Migration Plan

- Create `reporting_` models under `app/models/reporting/`
- Run migration to create materialized views
- Backfill: first refresh runs for all data (initial build, potentially slow)
- Deploy query layer changes (reporting controllers use materialized views)
- Schedule `RefreshMaterializedViewsJob` via Solid Queue recurring schedule
- Monitor query performance before and after
- Rollback: drop materialized views, remove models, revert query service changes

8. Risks & Mitigations

Risk: `REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW CONCURRENTLY` requires a unique index (added in migration) and acquires `SHARE UPDATE EXCLUSIVE` lock. If a refresh is still running when the next one starts, it will queue and potentially block.
Mitigation: Monitor refresh job duration. If refresh takes >15 minutes, increase the interval. Use a single-job lock (e.g., `Sidekiq::Lock` or `GoodJob::Lock`) to prevent overlapping executions.

Risk: Materialized view definition becomes invalid when the base schema changes (e.g., column rename on `amount_lines`)
Mitigation: Materialized views are managed by migrations. Any schema change to underlying tables must be accompanied by updating and refreshing the materialized views.

Risk: Materialized view data is up to 15 minutes stale — balance sheet queries may show stale data
Mitigation: This is acceptable for a cooperative banking system. End-of-day reports use the end-of-day refresh. Intra-day reports show near-real-time data. If a controller needs live data, it falls back to the live query.

9. Definition of Done

- 3 materialized views created: `reporting_trial_balances`, `reporting_balance_sheets`, `reporting_loan_agings`
- `RefreshMaterializedViewsJob` runs every 15 minutes via Solid Queue recurring schedule
- Refresh uses `CONCURRENTLY` with unique indexes
- `Reporting::TrialBalance`, `Reporting::BalanceSheet`, `Reporting::LoanAging` models exist
- Trial balance, balance sheet, and loan aging controllers use materialized views when available
- Fallback to live queries works when view is stale or unavailable
- RSpec tests verify: materialized view returns correct data, fallback works, refresh is non-blocking
- Query performance benchmark: trial balance query < 50ms on materialized view vs current performance
- All existing tests pass with no new failures

10. Codebase Implementation Details

10.1 File Manifest

- `db/migrate/*_create_reporting_materialized_views.rb` — new migration
- `app/models/reporting/trial_balance.rb` — new read-only model
- `app/models/reporting/balance_sheet.rb` — new read-only model
- `app/models/reporting/loan_aging.rb` — new read-only model
- `app/jobs/reporting/refresh_materialized_views_job.rb` — new recurring job
- `app/services/accounting/trial_balance_service.rb` — update to use materialized view
- `app/services/lending/aging_calculation_service.rb` — update to use materialized view

10.2 Existing Patterns to Follow

- Model: Follow `app/models/accounting/running_balance.rb` pattern — `self.table_name`, `readonly?`, scopes
- Service: Follow `ActiveInteraction::Base` pattern from `app/services/accounting/post_entry_service.rb`
- Job: Follow `app/jobs/application_job.rb` — `include CooperativeJob`, `queue_as :default`
- Reporting: Follow `app/services/accounting/trial_balance_service.rb` pattern

10.3 Migration

```ruby
class CreateReportingMaterializedViews < ActiveRecord::Migration[8.0]
  def up
    # Trial balance
    execute(<<~SQL)
      CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW reporting_trial_balances AS
      SELECT
        a.id AS account_id,
        a.account_code, a.name AS account_name, a.account_type,
        a.normal_credit_balance, a.cooperative_id,
        COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN al.amount_type = 0 THEN al.amount_cents WHEN al.amount_type = 1 THEN -al.amount_cents END), 0) AS balance_cents,
        COUNT(DISTINCT e.id) AS entry_count,
        MAX(e.posted_at) AS last_activity_at
      FROM accounting_accounts a
      LEFT JOIN accounting_amount_lines al ON al.account_id = a.id
      LEFT JOIN accounting_entries e ON e.id = al.entry_id AND e.status = 'posted'
      GROUP BY a.id, a.account_code, a.name, a.account_type, a.normal_credit_balance, a.cooperative_id
      ORDER BY a.account_code
    SQL

    # Balance sheet
    execute(<<~SQL)
      CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW reporting_balance_sheets AS
      SELECT
        COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN a.account_type = 'asset' THEN bal.balance_cents ELSE 0 END), 0) AS total_assets_cents,
        COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN a.account_type = 'liability' THEN bal.balance_cents ELSE 0 END), 0) AS total_liabilities_cents,
        COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN a.account_type = 'equity' THEN bal.balance_cents ELSE 0 END), 0) AS total_equity_cents,
        CURRENT_DATE AS as_of_date
      FROM accounting_accounts a
      JOIN accounting_running_balances bal ON bal.account_id = a.id
      WHERE bal.as_of_date = (SELECT MAX(as_of_date) FROM accounting_running_balances)
    SQL

    # Loan aging
    execute(<<~SQL)
      CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW reporting_loan_agings AS
      SELECT
        l.id AS loan_id, l.loan_number, l.cooperative_id,
        m.id AS member_id,
        CONCAT(m.last_name, ', ', m.first_name) AS member_name,
        l.outstanding_principal_cents,
        MAX(lp.payment_date) AS last_payment_date,
        CURRENT_DATE AS as_of_date
      FROM loans l
      JOIN members m ON m.id = l.member_id
      LEFT JOIN loan_payments lp ON lp.loan_id = l.id
      WHERE l.status IN ('active', 'disbursed')
      GROUP BY l.id, l.loan_number, l.cooperative_id, m.id, m.last_name, m.first_name, l.outstanding_principal_cents
    SQL

    # Unique indexes for concurrent refresh
    execute("CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_reporting_trial_balances ON reporting_trial_balances (account_id)")
    execute("CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_reporting_loan_agings ON reporting_loan_agings (loan_id)")
  end

  def down
    execute("DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW IF EXISTS reporting_trial_balances")
    execute("DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW IF EXISTS reporting_balance_sheets")
    execute("DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW IF EXISTS reporting_loan_agings")
  end
end
```

10.4 Read-Only Model

```ruby
module Reporting
  class TrialBalance < ApplicationRecord
    self.table_name = "reporting_trial_balances"
    self.primary_key = "account_id"

    belongs_to :account, class_name: "Accounting::Account"
    belongs_to :cooperative

    monetize :balance_cents

    def readonly?
      true
    end

    scope :by_cooperative, ->(coop) { where(cooperative_id: coop.id) }
    scope :by_type, ->(type) { where(account_type: type) }
    scope :with_balance, -> { where.not(balance_cents: 0) }
  end
end
```

10.5 Reporting Service Update

```ruby
# app/services/accounting/trial_balance_service.rb — updated
class Accounting::TrialBalanceService
  def call(cooperative:, as_of_date: Date.current)
    if use_materialized_view?
      Reporting::TrialBalance.by_cooperative(cooperative)
    else
      legacy_trial_balance(cooperative, as_of_date)
    end
  end

  private

  def use_materialized_view?
    Reporting::TrialBalance.any?
  end
end
```

